Next is coffee.​

I better hurry up before somebo—
Oh, my, ain't this place a godsend?

Anyways, my name's Eileen. I was just headed here from some volunteer work I was doin' outta' the next township over. God bless the volunteer work. Fantastic work, horrible coffee they had there, though. My god, was it dirt water. Couldn't down more than three cups of it, ha! It seriously was disgusting, really. I like to think coffee's kind of like art, hahahahaha! Coffee is kinda like art, I'm gonna write that down. Can't you see that on a T-shirt, or a...
*Eileen experiences a sudden crash in energy due to the high amounts of caffeine*
H-hello?
Oh my god, did she just...
*The protagonist pushes Eileen's coffee mug towards her mouth, reviving her energy*
...bumper sticker? If I can't come up with a catchy one-liner, hahahaha! Anyways, I do love the coffee selection they have here, truly can't get enough of it. I don't really drink it as much as other people, but I tell you, if I don't have a good cup in the morning, I'm not myself.​
Wait, is that clock right?
Oh my god, I forgot to pick my son up from daycare. How in the hell did that happen?
Goodness, I am so confused right now. That is wild, that is just... wild, they have hazelnut toffee light roast.​
I've never seen that before. Anyways, it's really nice to meet you. What'd you say your name was?
What're you, deaf?
I gotta skidaddle, but I'll pray for your ears. God, I need a refill, I feel like everything is in slow-motion right now.​

[WASHINGTON]

[HAMILTON]

[WASHINGTON]

[HAMILTON]
But—

[WASHINGTON]

Wild child

And now my eyes are open

When everything's wrong, you make it right
I feel so high, I come alive
I need to be free
